        <div class="row gy-5 g-xl-8 mt-1">
            <div class="col-lg-12">
                <!--begin: card-->
                <div class="card shadow-sm">
                    <!--begin :card header-->
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3 class="card-title">
                            <span class="fa fa-info-circle font-lg popovers btn-circle"></span>
                    &nbsp;What is roof pitch calculation?
                        </h3>
                    </div>
                    <!--end :card header-->
                    <!--begin :card body-->
                    <div class="card-body p-0">
                        <div class="row">
                            <!--begin :main section-->
                            <div class="col-md-12">
                                <div class="card-p ">
                            <p>Roof pitch is the measure of the slant of your roof. It is one of the many important elements of your roof, Roof pitch is one of the most visible aspects of a roof. It&rsquo;s the measure of the steepness of a roof, or its slope. Roof pitch is expressed as a ratio of the roof&rsquo;s vertical rise to its horizontal span, or &ldquo;run&rdquo;.</p>

                            <p>The most commonly used roof pitches fall in a range between 4/12 and 9/12. Pitches lower than 4/12 have a slight angle, and they are defined as low-slope roofs. Pitches of less than 2/12 are considered flat roofs, even though they may be very slightly angled.</p>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <!--end :main section-->
                        </div>
                        <hr />
                        
                        <div class="row card-body">
                            <div class="col-md-7">
                            <div class="table-responsive">
                            <h5 class="bold card-title">
                                Roof pitch calculation
                            </h5>
                            <blockquote>
                            <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Roof Pitch</mi></mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle="true"><mfrac><mi>N</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mfrac></math>
                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Slop</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>N</mi></mfrac><mo>&#xD7;</mo><mn>100</mn></math>
                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Angle</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#xA0;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>N</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>
                            </blockquote>
                            </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-5" align="center">
                        <img id="ctl00_cphPageContent_imgClayBricks" title="Roof pitch" data-bs-toggle="tooltip"
                              class="img img-fluid" src="~/ClinetPanel/img/Quantity-Estimator/RoofPitch.png" alt="Roof_pitch-Calculator" style="border-width:0px;">
                            </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                    <!--end :card body-->
                </div>
                <!--end :card -->
