<!-- begin : Page setiion 2  -->
<div class="row gy-5 g-xl-8 mt-1">
    <div class="col-lg-12">
        <!--begin: card-->
        <div class="card shadow-sm">
            <!--begin :card header-->
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3 class="card-title">
                    <span class="fa fa-info-circle font-lg popovers btn-circle"></span>
                    &nbsp;What are types of roof pitch?
                </h3>
            </div>
            <!--end :card header-->
            <!--begin :card body-->
            <div class="card-body p-0">
                <div class="row">
                    <!--begin :main section-->

                    <div class="col-md-12">
                        <div class="card-p">

                           <ul>
	<li><strong>1. Low Roof Pitch/Slope &ndash;</strong>&nbsp;This type of roof would have at least a 3:12 pitch, which means that a roof rises 3 feet for every 12 feet of its base horizontal length (not greater than5:12).Roofing: This type of roof is considered to be &ldquo;walk-able&ldquo;, and easy for performing a roof installation.</li>
	<li><strong>2. Medium Roof Pitch/Slope &ndash;</strong>&nbsp;The roof of this type would fall within 6:12 &ndash; 9:12 roofing slope range.Roofing: These roofs with intermediate pitch / average slope roofs are considered to be &ldquo;non walk-able&rdquo;, as they represent a higher degree of complexity, therefore they are more expensive to install. They require special equipment such as roofing jacks, and planks in order to be able to perform the roofing installation.</li>
	<li><strong>3. High/Steep Roof Pitch/Slope &ndash;</strong>&nbsp;Roofs in this category have a slope that is greater than 9 inches of rise for every foot of horizontal roof&rsquo;s run. Roofing: The high slopped roof is, perhaps, the most difficult and dangerous roofing surface to work on. You may expect to pay a higher price for this type of roof per square of installation. Any roof and especially steep roofs require the use of a special protections and fall arrest equipment.</li>
</ul>

                           
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!--end :main section-->

                </div>
            </div>
            <!--end :card body-->

        </div>
        <!--end: card-->

    </div>
</div>
